cs.CR, cs.EM, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the injection of transient faults to attack cryptographic implementations, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of electromagnetic fault injection as a method of attack suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of electromagnetics (cs.EM) or architecture (cs.AR). The study of the impact of electromagnetic glitch fault injection on a microcontroller suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
